{\par \b Syntax:}\par translation(Vector, Object)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Translates a geometric object along a given vector. The vector is given as the difference of two points (head-tail).\par
{\par \b Example:}\par translation(0-i, GA) translates object A down one unit.\par translation(GB-GA, GC) translates object C along the vector AB.\par }